        "comment": {
          "commentType": "PTM",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Capsid scaffolding protein: Capsid scaffolding protein is cleaved by assemblin after formation of the spherical procapsid. As a result, the capsid obtains its mature, icosahedral shape. Cleavages occur at two or more sites: release (R-site) and maturation (M-site)"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
